Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of perhaps part of bird (legs and added red on underbelly remaining) to left.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 461, no. B780)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0060) (Phase 1)
